P1.21 Per-Request Spending Override Implementation Notes:

Implementation completed: 2026-03-29

Changes:
- internal/providers/aws.go:
  - Added PerDeploymentBudgetUSD to planInfraInput struct
  - Added PerDeploymentBudgetUSD to createInfraInput struct
  - planInfra: Uses override when provided, validates <= global limit
  - createInfra: Uses override when provided, validates <= global limit
  - Logs when per-request override is used

- internal/providers/aws_test.go:
  - TestPlanInfra_PerRequestSpendingOverride with 3 subtests:
    - override_allows_lower_budget: tight budget blocks expensive plan
    - override_cannot_exceed_global: validation prevents bypass
    - valid_override_works: proper override succeeds

Key decisions:
- Override must be positive to be used (0 or negative = use global)
- Override cannot exceed global limit (security measure)
- Both planInfra and createInfra support override for consistency
- Override applies to per-deployment limit only, not monthly budget

Usage example:
{
  "app_description": "staging app",
  "expected_users": 100,
  "region": "us-east-1",
  "per_deployment_budget_usd": 50.00
}
